{
  "texts": [
    "With a regression study, we found that this is indeed the case.",
    "Taking scanpath length as the independent variable and FLA as the dependent variable, we observed a significant effect across all datasets, including ZuCo 1.0: the positive t-scores in Table 7 denote that that longer scanpaths result in higher FLA values.",
    "Notably, the t-score is higher on CELER L1 (92.36) than on EML (73.03), which indicates that longer scanpath sequences were easier to predict on the former dataset.",
    "This insight confirms that the more challenging data of EML make FLA improvements harder.",
    "Interestingly, the same conclusion can be drawn for FDA, although the increase of this metric in the \"w/o Fine-tuning\" setup was stable across datasets (cf."
  ]
}